values.text: Sometimes things aren't necessarily as bad as you perceive them. Things and events happen objectively in life, but their effects to us are often very subjective. For example, one may view stress as a negative feeling. But as many studies have pointed out, it can also be viewed as our body's mechanism to prepare for what's coming and rise up to the challenge.
